comments: e is the only positive real k for which k^n is greater than or equal to n^k for all positive real n.
links: Harry J. Smith, Table of n, a(n) for n=1,...,200
prog: (PARI) { default(realprecision, 100); e=exp(1); for (n=1, 200, write("b062277.txt", n, " ", floor(e^n / n^e)) ) } [From _Harry J. Smith_, Aug 03 2009]
author: _Henry Bottomley_, Jul 02 2001
